Used to be Fat Dog, but was bought by two of the bartenders and turned into Kung Fu. Went there on Friday which was the second day they had the doors open and I think the place looks great. We walked in from the back that still has the old fat dog sign but when inside you start to notice the suttle changes and then finally the name on the wall. Great new choice of drink selection and the owners are still up there serving everyone drinks. Small menu of main dishes and great choices on appetizers. Tried the wings and split a hotdog and burger and they were all great. A must go place.

This is the best sushi place in all over the Brooklyn. We love sushi and we tried a lot of different sushi places in Bensonhurst, Kings Hwy areas and downtown Brooklyn, non of them is even nearly as good as this place. The delivery service is nice. The the size of rolls and sushis is much bigger comparing what other places make, the taste is much better than in other sushi places, prices are much cheaper and service is also much better. I strongly recommend to try their rolls and sushis, once you try it, you will never go to other place.
